1 5. Members of the committee are entitled to be reimbursed for expenses incurred in the
2 performance of their duties, in the same manner as other state officials are
3 reimbursed, according to sections 44 - 08 - 04 and 54 - 06 - 09. If not otherwise employed
4 by the state of North Dakota, members of the committee are entitled to receive
5 per diem compensation of one hundred thirty-five dollars for each day of attending
6 meetings and performing other duties relating to official business of the committee.
7 SECTION 3. A new section to chapter 54-40.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
8 and enacted as follows:
9 Rural catalyst grant program - Eligibility - Use of funds - Postaward monitoring -
10 Report to legislative management and legislative assembly.
11 1. The department of commerce shall administer the rural catalyst grant program to
12 support quality of life improvement projects for rural communities in the state and
13 provide grant award recommendations to the rural catalyst committee.
14 2. Grant funding may be awarded for projects that will address a critical need in the
15 areas of art and culture, community and economic development, education, health and
16 wellness, or for the purpose of preserving or reopening rural grocery stores in a rural
17 community with a population of eight thousand five hundred or fewer individuals. The
18 maximum grant award under the program is five hundred thousand dollars.
19 3. To be eligible for a grant under the program, a grant recipient shall provide one dollar
20 of matching funds from nonstate sources for every two dollars provided from the rural
21 catalyst fund. Matching funds may be in the form of cash or in - kind contributions .
22 Pledges for matching funds may be considered for up to seven years.
23 4. By September first of each even - numbered year, the department shall submit a repor t
24 to the legislative management regarding the results of the program, including the
25 number of projects requested and supported through the program, information on
26 projects receiving funding, matching funds raised for each project, and how the project
27 has affected local communities. The department shall provide this report to the
28 appropriations committees of the next legislative assembly.
29 5. The department shall maintain a database on the department's website regarding data
30 and the status of each approved project.
